<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>The Mordechai Langsam Family</H1>
<A HREF="../hometree.htm">
<IMG SRC="../img/smaltree.gif" WIDTH=36 HEIGHT=35 BORDER=0 ALIGN="RIGHT" alt="Go Home"></A><BR><P>
<HR>
<P>

<TABLE border=10><TR><TD><FONT SIZE=+2>Mordechai Langsam</FONT> was known to have been a descendent of the <a href="../spira/bny-yscr.htm">Bnei Yissoschur, R' Hersh Mylech Spira</a>. This most likely places this branch in the L5 section of the "Langsam-Spira Family Tree" book, as many of those Langsams claim descent via both <a href="chaimleb.htm">Chaim Leib Langsam</a> and his brother, the Bnei Yissoschur. Mordechai had one known son. According to Mordechay (Moti) Pollack, Mordechai Langsam (1878 - 1953) was from Lesko, a son of Joseph, son of Yona Langsam. See his <a href="yona.pdf">email</a> describing this.
</TD></TR></TABLE><P>
<UL><LI><font size="+1"><B>Yitzchok</B></FONT> of Linsk had one known daughter.
        <UL>
        <LI><FONT COLOR="PURPLE">girl</FONT> married to Nocum Meir Heller.<BR> 
            <FONT COLOR="GREEN" SIZE=-1>Chana Sarah Weinreb</FONT>
        </UL>
  </UL>

